title: The Wenatchee Sasquatch: A Novella - MOBI
description:
FILE TYPE: MOBI

The Wenatchee Sasquatch is the debut novella by Martin Godfrey.

As fog blankets the wet and jagged forest floor of the Wenatchee state park, two Department of Agriculture field agents are met with horrific challenges. Their chances of survival are pushed to the limits.

Ben Randell and Veena Sangupta are sent out to investigate an invasive species that has destroyed forests throughout the country, the Asian Long-horned Beetle. While performing their search the dangers of the vast wilderness start to become life threateningly overwhelming.

The two agents are accompanied by Veena's boyfriend Nick and good friend Mia. With plans of a relaxing, week long assignment, Ben and the others soon realize that escaping the forest alive may prove to be impossible
